(183, '_transient_ti_about_plugin_info_amp', 'O:8:\"stdClass\":22:{s:4:\"name\";s:3:\"AMP\";s:4:\"slug\";s:3:\"amp\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"1.4.2\";s:6:\"author\";s:95:\"<a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp/graphs/contributors\">AMP Project Contributors</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/automattic\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:9:{s:6:\"google\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:37:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/google\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2adafb3bf578fd97d8d2ea1c2ccb3db3?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:6:\"Google\";}s:3:\"xwp\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:34:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/xwp\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/94486776b589f2de407f45c8c648e711?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:3:\"XWP\";}s:10:\"automattic\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/automattic\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/687b3bf96c41800814e3b93766444283?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:10:\"Automattic\";}s:11:\"westonruter\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:42:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/westonruter\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/989838a2534d491ccb184d5b8a654f99?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:12:\"Weston Ruter\";}s:10:\"swissspidy\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/swissspidy\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/609d6ee54dc13a51270cb99769535b82?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:15:\"Pascal Birchler\";}s:9:\"miinasikk\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:40:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/miinasikk\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d3d093358cc1bd088bdcdf6511bc19eb?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:10:\"Miina Sikk\";}s:12:\"ryankienstra\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:43:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ryankienstra\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/9056a7f3e47cce5f4f5c6bcf89cd8864?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:13:\"Ryan Kienstra\";}s:13:\"albertomedina\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:44:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/albertomedina\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c61e7d8efedcd6e9bf7a0c6025f80489?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:13:\"albertomedina\";}s:13:\"tweetythierry\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:44:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/tweetythierry\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:82:\"http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c70294be72623e3f8995ee4832f8d065?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:14:\"Thierry Muller\";}}s:12:\"requires_php\";s:3:\"5.4\";s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:108;i:4;i:16;i:3;i:15;i:2;i:11;i:1;i:50;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:200;s:15:\"support_threads\";i:117;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:83;s:15:\"active_installs\";i:400000;s:8:\"homepage\";s:18:\"https://amp-wp.org\";s:8:\"sections\";a:6:{s:11:\"description\";s:3502:\"<p>The <a href=\"http://amp.dev\" rel=\"nofollow\">AMP Project</a> is an open-source initiative aiming to make the web better for all. AMP enables web experiences that are consistently fast, beautiful and high-performing across distribution platforms. AMP formerly stood for “Accelerated Mobile Pages”, but now works completely across desktop and mobile. The official AMP plugin for WordPress supports fully integrated AMP publishing for WordPress sites, with robust capabilities and granular publisher controls.</p>\n<p>Features and capabilities provided by the plugin include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>AMP-first Experiences</strong>: enabling <a href=\"https://amp.dev/about/websites\" rel=\"nofollow\">full-site AMP experiences</a> without sacrificing the flexibility of the platform or the fidelity of content.</li>\n<li><strong>Core Theme Support</strong>: enabling AMP compatibility for all core themes, from Twenty Ten all the way through Twenty Twenty.</li>\n<li><strong>Compatibility Tool</strong>: when automatic conversion of markup to AMP is not possible, debug AMP validation errors with detailed information including the invalid markup and the specific components responsible on site (e.g theme, plugin, embed); validation errors are shown contextually with their respective blocks in the editor.</li>\n<li><strong>CSS Tree Shaking</strong>: automatically remove the majority of unused CSS to bring the total under AMP&#8217;s 50KB limit; when the total after tree shaking is still over this limit, prioritization is used so that the all-important theme stylesheet important is retained, leaving less important ones to be excluded (e.g. print styles).</li>\n<li>✨ <strong>AMP Stories</strong> (beta): the AMP plugin enables the creation, editing, and publishing of <a href=\"https://amp.dev/about/stories\" rel=\"nofollow\">AMP Stories</a> in WordPress; leverage the magic of storytelling the WordPress way!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The plugin can be configured to follow one of three different template modes: Standard, Transitional, and Reader. In Standard mode you use AMP as the framework for your site, and there need not be any separate AMP and non-AMP versions. When configured to operate in Reader and Transitional modes, a given page will have a canonical URL as well as a corresponding (paired) AMP URL. The AMP plugin is not serving as a mobile theme; it does not redirect mobile devices to the AMP version. Instead, the AMP version is served to mobile visitors when they find the content on platforms such as Twitter, Pinterest, Google Search, and others. Reader mode only supports serving AMP for singular posts, pages, and other post types, whereas Standard and Transitional mode support serving the entire site as AMP.</p>\n<p>With the official AMP plugin for WordPress, the WordPress ecosystem is provided with the capabilities and tools it needs to build world-class AMP experiences without deviating from its standard, flexible, and well-known content creation workflow.</p>\n<h3>Getting Started</h3>\n<p>To learn more about the plugin and start leveraging its capabilities to power your AMP content creation workflow check <a href=\"https://amp-wp.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">the official AMP plugin product site</a>.</p>\n<p>If you are a developer, we encourage you to <a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp\" rel=\"nofollow\">follow along</a> or <a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp/blob/develop/contributing.md\" rel=\"nofollow\">contribute</a> to the development of this plugin on GitHub.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:429:\"<ol>\n<li>Upload the folder to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n<li>If you currently use older versions of the plugin in <code>Reader</code> mode, it is strongly encouraged to migrate to <code>Transitional</code> or <code>Standard</code> mode. Depending on your theme/plugins, some development work may be required.</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:416:\"<p>Please see the <a href=\"https://amp-wp.org/documentation/frequently-asked-questions/\" rel=\"nofollow\">FAQs on amp-wp.org</a>. Don&#8217;t see an answer to your question? Please <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/amp/\">search the support forum</a> to see if someone has asked your question. Otherwise, please <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/amp/#new-post\">open a new support topic</a>.</p>\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:152:\"<p>For the plugin’s changelog, please see <a href=\"https://github.com/ampproject/amp-wp/releases\" rel=\"nofollow\">the Releases page on GitHub</a>.</p>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:6558:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Create great web experiences via AMP-powered websites or visually rich, engaging stories.\"></a><p>Create great web experiences via AMP-powered websites or visually rich, engaging stories.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2108964\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2108964\" alt=\"Story editor enables creation of pages in a horizontal, page-based interface, with background media, with blocks that can be dragged, rotated, and animated.\"></a><p>Story editor enables creation of pages in a horizontal, page-based interface, with background media, with blocks that can be dragged, rotated, and animated.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme&#039;s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.\"></a><p>In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme\'s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"All core themes are supported, and many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.\"></a><p>All core themes are supported, and many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Reader mode templates are still available, but they are differ from the active theme.\"></a><p>Reader mode templates are still available, but they are differ from the active theme.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen.\"></a><p>Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Standard mode: Using AMP as the framework for your site, not having to maintain an AMP and non-AMP version. Mobile and desktop users get same experience.\"></a><p>Standard mode: Using AMP as the framework for your site, not having to maintain an AMP and non-AMP version. Mobile and desktop users get same experience.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Transitional mode: A path to making your site fully AMP-compatible, with tools to assist with debugging validation issues along the way.\"></a><p>Transitional mode: A path to making your site fully AMP-compatible, with tools to assist with debugging validation issues along the way.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.\"></a><p>Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.\"></a><p>Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2183573\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2183573\" alt=\"The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.\"></a><p>The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2193061\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2193061\" alt=\"Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.\"></a><p>Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2193061\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2193061\" alt=\"Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.\"></a><p>Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-14.png?rev=2193061\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-14.png?rev=2193061\" alt=\"Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 50KB of inline CSS.\"></a><p>Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 50KB of inline CSS.</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-15.png?rev=2193061\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-15.png?rev=2193061\" alt=\"A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.\"></a><p>A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:14716:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">504 error</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nesdam1981\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f50699db8a690b904215a0256ee6612b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f50699db8a690b904215a0256ee6612b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nesdam1981\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Nesdam1981</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">January 26, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><strong>After troubleshooting by deactivating and activating all my plugins one by one several times and discussing the issue with my web host</strong> I can confirm that this plugin causes \"504 Gateway Time-Out\" error. Whenever this plugin is activated I cannot activate or create posts without getting the error.\nI can also add that I have several domains that result in the same error with this plugin and gives no errors when the plugin is deactivated.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Wonderful plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/vinayras\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f67f011ca63bd62ff4cf40e9aa074e7c?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f67f011ca63bd62ff4cf40e9aa074e7c?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/vinayras\" class=\"reviewer-name\">vinayras</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">January 3, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">A must-have plugin for my websites. This plugin has taken care of everything one needs for going AMP with existing themes. </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Fast but flawed.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/4waam\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3a815ea9e265e09f11fd1db2edae396d?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3a815ea9e265e09f11fd1db2edae396d?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/4waam\" class=\"reviewer-name\">4waam</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">January 2, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I really wanted this to work. It ran the pages really fast. I think Google pads the data for how fast to make it seem better than it is.\n\nThe real problem is that it is super difficult to get auto ads to work with this plugin. I spent hours with different plugins, options, following help guides and not one actually was able to display ads from Google adsense. Turn the plugin off and ads are back. \n\nAs much as I want lighter and nimbler the site has to make money. This plugin prevented me from doing that.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Grate Plugin, thanks!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/macaway\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/86e4ddef12a1e0a68eb919b8e3b2317c?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/86e4ddef12a1e0a68eb919b8e3b2317c?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/macaway\" class=\"reviewer-name\">macaway</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 28, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">A great plugin, thank you so much!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">AMP Plugin is easy to use</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kamalh\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a37c287d2d351e1c7331942d1985ce47?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a37c287d2d351e1c7331942d1985ce47?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kamalh\" class=\"reviewer-name\"> <small>(KamalH)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 16, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">There is not much one needs to do while using the official AMP plugin. You need to install and activate the plugin. It does the job for you!\n\nThe best thing about the plugin is the outstanding support you can get on the support forum. James Osborne was very helpful in many of the topics I created.\n\nI would definitely recommend this plugin if you want to implement AMP on your website.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Excellent Support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bramesh\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2ce5bb63d96ad0467556deaabba504a6?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2ce5bb63d96ad0467556deaabba504a6?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/bramesh\" class=\"reviewer-name\">bramesh</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 12, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Great Plugin and Excellent Support due to which will be able to convert my site in AMP very Soon !!\n\nCheers to Support team !!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Good support, Plugin needs improvements.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/naveendsouza\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5fb7f95c6ba26bfb3c3f0059e369aa27?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5fb7f95c6ba26bfb3c3f0059e369aa27?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/naveendsouza\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Naveen Dsouza <small>(naveendsouza)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 12, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Plugin\'s contributors provide good support and provided solution for my question in support forum regarding webp images support.\nPlugin needs improvements like support for <code>&lt;picture&gt;</code> element which is introduced in HTML5. I will request plugin contributors to add support for picture element ASAP.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">AMP well its needed</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/patrick_d1985\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5c556888a0e049f5f824bbd27f4c455f?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5c556888a0e049f5f824bbd27f4c455f?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/patrick_d1985\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Patrick_D1985</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 3, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">AMP simply put is needed as not everyone in the whole wide world will always be on a great connection. That is the main reason I have to use AMP.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">it&#039;s broke my site..</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/siliconwebx\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/51bd2de585ff9bce62663cde622acf41?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/51bd2de585ff9bce62663cde622acf41?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/siliconwebx\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Silicon WebX <small>(siliconwebx)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">November 30, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">it\'s broke my site..</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Duplicate Featured Image need to fix</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/huixia0010\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3e43176bb89d53e50d122cb3ac884b85?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3e43176bb89d53e50d122cb3ac884b85?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/huixia0010\" class=\"reviewer-name\">huixia0010</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">November 16, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Duplicate Featured Image, and no option to disable single not show Featured Image.\nPlease add this option in this plugin. Thank you.\nMy temporary solution is delete <code>&lt;?php $this-&gt;load_parts( [ &#039;featured-image&#039; ] ); ?&gt;</code>\nfrom <code>wp-content/plugins/amp/templates/single.php</code></div>\n</div>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:149:\"Official AMP plugin, supported by the AMP team. Formerly Accelerated Mobile Pages, AMP enables great experiences across mobile, desktop, and stories.\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.1.4.2.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:15:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:89:\"Create great web experiences via AMP-powered websites or visually rich, engaging stories.\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:156:\"Story editor enables creation of pages in a horizontal, page-based interface, with background media, with blocks that can be dragged, rotated, and animated.\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:179:\"In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme\'s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:191:\"All core themes are supported, and many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.\";}i:5;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:85:\"Reader mode templates are still available, but they are differ from the active theme.\";}i:6;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:80:\"Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen.\";}i:7;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:153:\"Standard mode: Using AMP as the framework for your site, not having to maintain an AMP and non-AMP version. Mobile and desktop users get same experience.\";}i:8;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:136:\"Transitional mode: A path to making your site fully AMP-compatible, with tools to assist with debugging validation issues along the way.\";}i:9;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:120:\"Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.\";}i:10;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:138:\"Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when: no issues are found, new issues need review, or issues block AMP from being served.\";}i:11;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2183573\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.\";}i:12;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2193061\";s:7:\"caption\";s:167:\"Each Validated URL shows the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether invalid markup is removed or kept. Keeping invalid markup disables AMP.\";}i:13;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-13.png?rev=2193061\";s:7:\"caption\";s:164:\"Each validation error provides a stack trace to identify which code is responsible for the invalid markup, whether a theme, plugin, embed, content block, and so on.\";}i:14;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-14.png?rev=2193061\";s:7:\"caption\";s:143:\"Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 50KB of inline CSS.\";}i:15;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-15.png?rev=2193061\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.\";}}s:8:\"versions\";a:31:{s:3:\"0.2\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.2.zip\";s:3:\"0.3\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.2\"